                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <desc>The manuscript can be dated to the fourteenth or fifteenth century based on palaeographic features. For example, the letter መ shows a tendency for loop separations, ሎ demonstrates the
                                    vowel marker with a linking line, ጵ exhibits the form used before the sixteenth century. Additionally, the word እግዚአብሔር is 
                                    written as a single word. Overall, the manuscript displays the standard orthography 
                                    of medieval Ethiopic. </desc>
                               <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
